````

---

🎯 Why Functions are Important

✔ Reduce code repetition
✔ Improve readability
✔ Simplify debugging
✔ Enable modular programming

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 Creating a Function

Functions are created using the `def` keyword.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 Syntax

```python id="function_syntax"
def function_name():
    # code
```

---

💻 Example

```python id="simple_function"
def greet():
    print("Welcome to Python")

greet()
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="simple_function_output"
Welcome to Python
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📥 Function Parameters

Parameters allow functions to receive input values.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="parameter_example"
def greet(name):
    print("Hello", name)

greet("Saakshi")
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="parameter_output"
Hello Saakshi
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔄 return Statement

`return` sends a value back from the function.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="return_example"
def add(a, b):
    return a + b

result = add(10, 20)

print(result)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="return_output"
30
```

---

📌 Difference Between print() and return

| `print()`          | `return`            |
| ------------------ | ------------------- |
| Displays output    | Sends value back    |
| Cannot reuse value | Value can be reused |

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔢 Default Parameters

Functions can have default values.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

💻 Example

```python id="default_parameter"
def greet(name="Guest"):
    print("Hello", name)

greet()
greet("Python")
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="default_output"
Hello Guest
Hello Python
```

