⚡ Lambda Functions

Lambda functions are anonymous one-line functions.

---

🔹 Syntax

```python id="lambda_syntax"
lambda arguments : expression
```

---

💻 Example

```python id="lambda_example"
square = lambda x: x * x

print(square(5))
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="lambda_output"
25
```

---

💻 Lambda with Multiple Arguments

```python id="lambda_multiple"
add = lambda a, b: a + b

print(add(10, 20))
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="lambda_multiple_output"
30
```

